 The Nigerian Government has announced the closure of all land borders into the country for four weeks in a bid to curtail the spread of Coronavirus. The announcement was made by the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 on Monday. Also, the weekly Federal Executive Council meeting was suspended until further notice. Secretary to the Government of the Federation, who doubles as Chairman of the Presidential Task Force on -COVID-19, Boss Mustapha, revealed that civil servants will be instructed on how to operate soon. Nigeria now has 36 confirmed cases of the virus with one recorded death so far.